  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study examines associations between competence in cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT) and
      adherence to evidence-based generic CBT in therapists and treatment outcome in patients with
      depression or an anxiety disorder in psychiatric outpatient care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
